node.title: List of Auckland Omicron-related locations of interest grows
node.description: A number of close contact Omicron-related locations of interest in Auckland and Nelson have been added to the Ministry of Health's website today.
node.content:
["A number of close contact Omicron-related locations of interest in Auckland and Nelson have been added to the Ministry of Health's website today.", "", "
\nPhoto: AFP\n
", "Several Auckland locations have been listed as requiring people to get tested immediately and on day five if they were exposed at the specified time.", "In Motueka, anyone who was at Greenwood Health Motueka on 21 January between 11.40am and 1.45pm is asked to isolate, get tested immediately and then again on day five.", "Other suspected Omicron locations of interest where people should monitor themselves for 10 days after being exposed to the site and get a test if symptoms develop include Nelson Airport Terminal Building, Event Cinemas in Westfield Albany and Rainbow's End in Manukau.", "For an up to date list of all locations of interest check the Ministry of Health's website.", "The Ministry of Health said that to date, there are 19 community cases of Covid-19 associated with the January Omicron cluster and all are in isolation."]
